OL,6,FHe described his mother Mary as a
OL,7,Fwoman with a strong Catholic faith, a
OL,8,Fstrong work ethic and a "deep sense of
OL,9,Ffamily values and she lived these out
OL,10,Fevery day".
OL,12,FBorn in Co Cork, he said she trained
OL,13,Fto be a nurse and then a midwife
OL,14,Fbefore meeting his father Mick and
OL,15,Fsettling together on a dairy farm in
OL,16,FBeragh ` where they had 11 children.
OL,18,F"No-one was ever turned away from her
OL,19,Fdoor and no-one left without a cup of
OL,20,Ftea or some of her beautiful current
OL,21,Fbread or apple tart," he said.
OL,26,@pD@YOUrD@JO]zD@AOU}D@UO]
