OL,3,CFamily robbed of three generations by
OL,4,COmagh atrocity 'hope no others suffer'
OL,6,F"A modest women all her days, our
OL,7,Fmother let her actions and her endless
OL,8,Fcompassion speak for her.
OL,10,F"She was happiest in the kitchen
OL,11,Fsurrounded by her family.
OL,13,F"Her tragic passing in the cruellest
OL,14,Fof ways possible, the Omagh bomb,
OL,15,Frobbed us, her family, her husband,
OL,16,Ffriends and neighbours a chance to pay
OL,17,Fback the love and affection she had
OL,18,Fshown to all of her.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUuD@AOU
