OL,3,CFamily robbed of three generations by
OL,4,COmagh atrocity 'hope no others suffer'
OL,6,F"Maura may have left this world too
OL,7,Fsoon, but she will forever remain a
OL,8,Fshining light for us and we have no
OL,9,Fdoubt that the world would have been a
OL,10,Fbetter place had she lived," she said.
OL,12,FAoibheann said her mother grew up in
OL,13,Fthe farmlands of Beragh with nine
OL,14,Fbrothers, one sister and her parents,
OL,15,Fwith a love of camogie and Irish
OL,16,Fdancing, and went on to meet her
OL,17,Fhusband-to-be Michael at Kelly's in
OL,18,FBallygawley.
