OL,3,CFamily robbed of three generations by
OL,4,COmagh atrocity 'hope no others suffer'
OL,6,F"On the day of our granny's 66th
OL,7,Fbirthday, they travelled to Omagh to
OL,8,Fcelebrate when fate intervened. The
OL,9,FOmagh bomb stole our mummy from her
OL,10,Floved ones, leaving behind a grieving
OL,11,Fhusband and three of her children aged
OL,12,Fonly five, four and three, as well as
OL,13,Fthe wide Monaghan and Grimes families.
OL,15,F"Her mother, Mary Grimes, her youngest
OL,16,Fdaughter Maura, as well as Eimear and
OL,17,FEvelyn were all taken from us that
OL,18,Fday."
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@AOUzD@EO]
